{"title": "Cooking for Salud!: Creamy Herb Dip (with almonds) - Olivewood Gardens", "author": "Olivewood", "url": "https://www.olivewoodgardens.org/creamy-herb-dip-with-almonds/", "hostname": "olivewoodgardens.org", "description": "Cooking for Salud! Creamy Herb Dip (with almonds) Created by Chef Marguerite Grifka Ingredients 1 cup water 3 Tablespoons olive oil 1 lemon, juiced 1 clove garlic \u00bd teaspoon salt \u00bc teaspoon black pepper 1 Tablespoon dijon mustard 1 teaspoon celery seeds \u00bd cup blanched almonds, soaked overnight 3 green onions, green tops chopped separate ...", "sitename": "Olivewood Gardens and Learning Center", "date": "2014-02-14", "id": null, "license": null, "body": null, "comments": "", "commentsbody": null, "raw_text": null, "text": "[Cooking for Salud!: Creamy Herb Dip (with almonds)](https://www.olivewoodgardens.org/creamy-herb-dip-with-almonds/)\nCooking for Salud!\nCreamy Herb Dip (with almonds)\nCreated by Chef Marguerite Grifka\nIngredients\n1 cup water\n3 Tablespoons olive oil\n1 lemon, juiced\n1 clove garlic\n\u00bd teaspoon salt\n\u00bc teaspoon black pepper\n1 Tablespoon dijon mustard\n1 teaspoon celery seeds\n\u00bd cup blanched almonds, soaked overnight\n3 green onions, green tops chopped separate from white bottoms\n1 Tablespoon dry herbs or 3 Tablespoons fresh parsley, cilantro, dill, basil or any combination of fresh herbs\nDirections\n1. Drain almonds and put in blender with lemon juice, the white bottom of green onions, garlic, celery seed, salt, pepper, mustard, and \u00bd cup of water. Pulse to grind. Slowly add remaining water as needed to keep things moving.\n2. Drizzle the olive oil in slowly while blending the dip. When mixture is smooth check for seasoning, add the herbs, green onion top and any additional salt or pepper. Pulse to combine. Chill well and enjoy with vegetables.\n\u2022\u2022\u2022\u2022\u2022\nCooking for Salud!\nDip Cremoso de Hierbas (con almendras)\nCreada por la Chef Marguerite Grifka\nIngredientes\n1 taza de agua\n3 cucharadas de aceite de oliva\n1 lim\u00f3n, jugo\n1 diente de ajo\n\u00bd cucharadita de sal\n\u00bc cucharadita de pimienta negra\n1 cucharada de mostaza dijon\n1 cucharadita de semillas de apio\n\u00bd taza de almendras peladas, remojadas durante toda la noche\n3 cebollas verdes, picar la parte verde separada de la parte blanca\n1 cucharada de hierbas secas o 3 cucharadas de perejil fresco, cilantro, eneldo, albahaca o cualquier combinaci\u00f3n de hierbas frescas\nInstrucciones\n1. Escurra las almendras, p\u00e9lelas y p\u00f3ngalas en la licuadora con el jugo de lim\u00f3n, la parte blanca de las cebollas verdes, el ajo, las semillas de apio, la sal, la pimienta, la mostaza y \u00bd taza de agua. Pulse para moler. Poco a poco agregue el resto del agua, seg\u00fan sea necesario para mantener la mezcla en movimiento.\n2. Lentamente deje caer el aceite de oliva mientras se mezcla el dip. Cuando la mezcla est\u00e9 suave cheque el sazon, agregue las hierbas, la parte verde de la cebolla y cualquier sal o pimienta adicional. Pulse para combinar. Enfr\u00ede bien y disfr\u00fatelo con vegetales.", "language": null, "image": null, "pagetype": "article", "links": ["https://www.olivewoodgardens.org/", "https://www.olivewoodgardens.org/esp/", "http://www.facebook.com/pages/Olivewood-Gardens-and-Learning-Center/322524662312", "https://www.instagram.com/olivewoodgardens", "https://www.linkedin.com/company/olivewood-gardens-learning-center", "http://www.olivewoodgardens.org/kitchenistas-portal/", "http://www.olivewoodgardens.org/contact-us/", "https://lp.constantcontactpages.com/su/NoEOOWR/Newsletter", "https://www.olivewoodgardens.org/donate/", "https://www.olivewoodgardens.org", "https://www.olivewoodgardens.org/about/", "https://www.olivewoodgardens.org/about/our-mission/", "https://www.olivewoodgardens.org/about/impact-annual-report/", "https://www.olivewoodgardens.org/about/our-board/", "https://www.olivewoodgardens.org/about/our-staff/", "htt